-----------------------------------------------------------
    Informal Modelling
-----------------------------------------------------------
- set of items I
	- each item i E I
		- weight w_i
		- value v_i
- capacity K for knapsack
- find subset of items in I that
	- has max value
	- sum of weights don't exceed K

-----------------------------------------------------------
    Modelling techniques
-----------------------------------------------------------
- choose some #decision variables#
	- encodes the result we're interested in
- express problem constraints in terms of these variables
- express the objective function
- it is a declarative formulation
	- specify 

-----------------------------------------------------------
    Formal Modelling
-----------------------------------------------------------
- decision variables
	- x_i denotes whether item is selected in the solution
		- x_i = 1 means item is selected
		- x_i = 0 means otherwise
- problem constraints
	- sum(every i in I) {w_i * x_i} <= K
- objective function
	- sum(every i in I) {v_i * x_i}
- maximize objective function subject to the problem constraint
